import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import geopandas as gpd
from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import make_axes_locatable

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['id'] = pd.to_datetime(data['id'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['id'])]

    us_shapefile = gpd.read_file('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PublicaMundi/MappingAPI/master/data/geojson/us-states.json')
    us_shapefile = us_shapefile.rename(columns={'postal': 'state'})
    data = data.merge(us_shapefile, on='state')

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(15, 25))
    divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)
    cax = divider.append_axes("right", size="5%", pad=0.1)

    data.boundary.plot(ax=ax, linewidth=1)
    data.plot(column='rate', ax=ax, legend=True, cax=cax, cmap='coolwarm', edgecolor='black', linewidth=0.5)

    plt.title('What is the distribution of obesity rates across different states?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['id'] = pd.to_datetime(data['id'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['id'])]
    data['id'] = data['id'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='id', y='rate', hue='state', data=data, legend='brief')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('How does the obesity rate vary over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Obesity Rate')
    plt.legend(title='State', loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 1))

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['id'] = pd.to_datetime(data['id'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['id'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='state', y='rate', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.axhline(data['rate'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"National Average: {data['rate'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the average obesity rate across all states?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("State")
    plt.ylabel("Obesity Rate")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['id'] = pd.to_datetime(data['id'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['id'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='rate', y='income_level', hue='state', data=data)

    plt.ylabel('Income Level')

chart = plot(data)
